<Legal
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Danamo Tech Ltd handles personal data on the WIFI.OS platform, under Kenya's Data Protection Act, 2019."
  version="2026-07-01"
  updated="1 July 2026"
>
  <p>
    <b>Danamo Tech Ltd</b> operates WIFI.OS. This policy explains what personal data we
    hold, why, and what you can do about it. It is written under the Data Protection Act,
    2019 (Kenya).
  </p>

  <h2>Two kinds of people</h2>
  <p>
    We handle data about two different groups, and the distinction matters because our
    obligations differ.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <b>ISPs</b> — our customers. We are the data controller for their account data.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>The ISP's customers</b> — the people buying internet. The ISP is the controller;
      we are a <b>processor</b> acting on their instructions.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we hold about an ISP</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Name, email address, phone number, county, and company name.</li>
    <li>The settlement account you ask us to pay you into.</li>
    <li>Your ledger: payments collected for you, our fees, and your payouts.</li>
    <li>
      An audit trail of significant actions taken in your console — who changed what, and
      when. We keep this because it is what lets us answer a payment dispute honestly.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we hold about an ISP's customers</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Phone number (this is how M-Pesa identifies a payment).</li>
    <li>What they bought, when, and for how much.</li>
    <li>Device MAC address and session records, so the router knows who is online.</li>
    <li>For PPPoE clients: name, account number, and service address, if the ISP records one.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We collect this to make the service work — to take a payment, to put someone online, and
    to cut them off when their time is up. We do not sell it. We do not market to an ISP's
    customers. We do not use it to train anything.
  </p>

  <h2>Who we share it with</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <b>Safaricom (M-Pesa Daraja)</b> — to request and confirm payments. A phone number and
      an amount necessarily go to them.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Our infrastructure providers</b> — to host the platform. They process data on our
      instructions and may not use it themselves.
    </li>
    <li><b>Nobody else</b>, unless the law requires it of us.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
  <p>
    Financial records are kept for seven years, because tax law requires it. Session and
    device records are kept for twelve months. If an ISP closes its account, we delete or
    anonymise what we are not legally required to keep.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Passwords are hashed, never stored in a form anybody can read.</li>
    <li>
      Your session lives in a cookie your browser will not hand to JavaScript, so a
      compromised page cannot steal it.
    </li>
    <li>
      Changing where we pay you requires a code sent to your email — an inbox the console
      itself cannot reach.
    </li>
    <li>Every ISP's data is isolated from every other ISP's, and access is audited.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Under the Data Protection Act you may ask us for a copy of your data, ask us to correct
    it, ask us to delete it (where we are not required to keep it), or object to how we use
    it. Write to us and we will respond within the statutory period. You may also complain
    to the Office of the Data Protection Commissioner.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Danamo Tech Ltd, Nairobi, Kenya — privacy@wifios.co.ke</p>
</Legal>
